<topic id="preferences-editor-diagram">
  <title><ph product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">Text </ph>Diagram Preferences</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm product="developer editor">Preferences<indexterm>Diagram</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">Preferences<indexterm>Text
            Diagram</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm product="developer editor">Diagram preferences</indexterm>
        <indexterm product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">Text Diagram preferences</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>For certain XML languages, <ph keyref="product"/> provides a diagram view as part of the
        <uicontrol>Text</uicontrol> mode editor. To configure the <uicontrol>Diagram</uicontrol>
      preferences, <ph conkeyref="reusables-preferences-pages/open-the-preferences-page"/> and go to
        <menucascade product="developer editor">
        <uicontrol>Editor</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol>Edit modes</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol>Text</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol>Diagram</uicontrol>
      </menucascade><menucascade product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">
        <uicontrol>Editor</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol>Edit modes / Pages</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol>Text Diagram</uicontrol>
      </menucascade>.</p>
    <p>The following options are available in this preference page:<dl>
        <dlentry id="show-full-model">
          <dt><uicontrol>Show Full Model XML Schema diagram</uicontrol></dt>
          <dd>When this option is selected, the <uicontrol>Text</uicontrol> mode editor for XML
            Schemas includes a split-screen view that shows a diagram of the schema structure. This
            is useful for seeing the effects of schema changes you make. For editing a schema using
            a diagram instead of text, use the <xref href="xml-schema-diagram-introduction.dita"
              >schema <uicontrol>Design</uicontrol> view</xref>.<note>When handling very large
              schemas, displaying the schema diagram might affect the performance of your system. In
              such cases, disabling the schema diagram view improves the speed of navigation through
              the edited schema.</note></dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><uicontrol>Enable Relax NG diagram and related views</uicontrol></dt>
          <dd>
            <p>Enables the Relax NG schema diagram and synchronization with the related views (<xref
                href="attributes-panel.dita#attributes-panel"
                ><uicontrol>Attributes</uicontrol></xref>, <xref href="model-panel.dita#model-panel"
                  ><uicontrol>Model</uicontrol></xref>, <xref
                href="text-elements-view.dita#text-elements-view"
                ><uicontrol>Elements</uicontrol></xref>, <xref
                href="relax-ng-schema-diagram-outline-view.dita#relax-ng-schema-diagram-outline-view"
                  ><uicontrol>Outline</uicontrol></xref>).</p>
            <p>
              <dl>
                <dlentry>
                  <dt><uicontrol>Show Relax NG diagram</uicontrol></dt>
                  <dd>Displays the Relax NG schema diagram in the split-screen views (<xref
                      href="relax-ng-schema-diagram-full-model-view.dita#relax-ng-schema-diagram-full-model-view"
                        ><uicontrol>Full Model View</uicontrol></xref> and <xref
                      href="relax-ng-schema-diagram-logical-model-view.dita#relax-ng-schema-diagram-logical-model-view"
                        ><uicontrol>Logical Model View</uicontrol></xref>).</dd>
                </dlentry>
              </dl>
            </p>
          </dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><uicontrol>Enable NVDL diagram and related views</uicontrol></dt>
          <dd>
            <p>Enables the NVDL schema diagram and synchronization with the related views (<xref
                href="attributes-panel.dita#attributes-panel"
                ><uicontrol>Attributes</uicontrol></xref>, <xref href="model-panel.dita#model-panel"
                  ><uicontrol>Model</uicontrol></xref>, <xref
                href="text-elements-view.dita#text-elements-view"
                ><uicontrol>Elements</uicontrol></xref>, <xref
                href="nvdl-schema-diagram-outline-view.dita#nvdl-schema-diagram-outline-view"
                  ><uicontrol>Outline</uicontrol></xref>).</p>
            <p>
              <dl>
                <dlentry>
                  <dt><uicontrol>Show NVDL diagram</uicontrol></dt>
                  <dd>Displays the NVDL schema diagram in the split-screen views (<xref
                      href="nvdl-schema-diagram-full-model-view.dita#nvdl-schema-diagram-full-model-view"
                        ><uicontrol>Full Model View</uicontrol></xref> and <xref
                      href="nvdl-logical-model.dita#nvdl-logical-model"><uicontrol>Logical Model
                        View</uicontrol></xref>).</dd>
                </dlentry>
              </dl>
            </p>
          </dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><uicontrol>Location relative to editor</uicontrol></dt>
          <dd>Allows you to specify the location of the schema diagram panel relative to the diagram
              <uicontrol>Text</uicontrol> editor.</dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><uicontrol>Show/Hide Annotations</uicontrol> link</dt>
          <dd>Use this link to navigate to the <xref
              href="preferences-editor-schema.dita#preferences-editor-schema/show-annotation"
                ><uicontrol>Schema Design</uicontrol> preferences page</xref> where you can choose
            to show or hide annotations in schema diagrams.</dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry product="developer editor">
          <dt><uicontrol>Zoom</uicontrol> link</dt>
          <dd>Use this link to navigate to the <xref
              href="preferences-editor-schema.dita#preferences-editor-schema/zoom"><uicontrol>Schema
                Design</uicontrol> preferences page</xref> where you can adjust the default zoom
            level of schema diagrams.</dd>
        </dlentry>
      </dl></p>
  </body>
